['472.                                  \xa0                     HENRY                      JORDAN                                                                                                          was indicted for                                                          feloniously being found at large before the expiration of the term for which he had been ordered to be transported            , April the 6th                  .', " See original\xa0The Record of the prisoner's conviction for a capital felony was produced and read, and also his majesty's pardon on condition of transportation for fourteen years, which had been accepted of by the prisoner.", ' \xa0                  PERCIVAL                   PHILLIPS                                                                                        sworn.', 'I am a constable; I belong to Sir                \xa0                  John                   Fielding                                                                                       ; I know the prisoner; he was tried for a highway robbery upon Mr. Hoare; I apprehended him; I am sure he is the man.', ' \xa0                  MATTHEW                   RICHMOND                                                                                        sworn.', 'I produced the watch when the prisoner was tried; I am sure he is the man that was tried for robbing Mr. Hoare.', ' \xa0                  JONATHAN                   BUTTERWORTH                                                                                        sworn.', "I had a letter from Sir                \xa0                  John                   Fielding                                                                                       , informing me that the prisoner had made his escape, and ordering me to make diligent search after him; I took him the next day at Manchester, making a woman's shoe.", "PRISONER's DEFENCE.", "When I came from on board of ship, I did it for fear of my life; there were twelve of us upon deck, and one Smith threatened to cut every one's throat that would not go into the boat, and come on shore. I went down to Manchester to follow my business.", '                                                      GUILTY            .                                                          DEATH            .', 'Tried by the Second Middlesex Jury before Mr. RECORDER.']